With stunning views and a beachfront location, it is widely considered the best finishing hole in golf.

But today, Pebble Beach's iconic 18th hole looks a bit different from usual after a ferocious storm uprooted one of the two Cypress trees dotting the fairway.

The trees, which were planted near the landing area in 2004 in the place of another pair of diseased trees, play into the strategy of the tee shot at the hole in the California coastal resort.

