The competition is due to be played from February 12 to 15, 2015.

The tree is the third to fall on a golf course in 2014. Earlier this year, the Eisenhower Tree on the 17th hole at Augusta National was completely damaged in an ice storm in February.

Meanwhile, an overhanging tree at the sixth hole at TPC Sawgrass, was cut down in October.

